Isolation: Do not read or modify files outside paths unblocked by .cursorignore, EXCEPT that running `Commit-AndPush.ps1` is explicitly allowed when the user requests commit/push operations.

Proof of Work: For every task, provide terminal-based verification (e.g., ls or rg) showing restricted directories like /Platforms/ or /Resources/ were not accessed.

No Assumptions: Do not implement standard MAUI patterns (MVVM, DI, etc.) unless explicitly requested and siloed.

Git Commit/Push Rule: When the user asks to commit, push, or "commit and push", always use `Commit-AndPush.ps1` instead of direct `git add`, `git commit`, or `git push` commands.
